<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870227-0084 </DOCNO><HL> Houston Oil Trust's Reserves</HL><DD> 02/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HO </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Houston Oil Trust said an independent engineering concern slashed the trust's estimated future revenue from its proved oil and gas reserves 44% to $88 million.    The study, which was prepared by Keplinger andamp; Associates Inc., Houston, was based on oil and gas prices and costs as of Oct. 31, 1986.    The oil and gas trust said the most &quot;significant factor&quot; contributing to the lower estimates was the decline in oil and gas prices. </TEXT></DOC>